3. Addresses wide population: Yes, this is a paid advertisement targeting 35,000-40,000 people in Neamț county
4. Electoral objective: Yes, explicitly calls for votes ("Pe 1 decembrie, votați USR, poziția 1 pe buletinul de vot!")
5. Journalism: No, this is clearly campaign material, not journalistic content
6. Personal opinion: No, this is an organized campaign message with CMF number
This post appears to be legitimate parliamentary election propaganda, as: - It focuses on parliamentary elections scheduled for December 1 - The propaganda period for parliamentary elections is still ongoing - There's no specific mention of the presidential race or candidate - The message is about local campaign activities and parliamentary voting

conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis: This appears to be legitimate parliamentary election propaganda because: - It explicitly targets the December 1 parliamentary elections - Contains required CMF number - Makes no mention of presidential candidates or presidential election - Focuses on local campaign activities - The parliamentary election campaign period is still active and allowed
